reviews.text:
If you're a fan of hot pot and good quality vegetables, you will enjoy this place as much as i did! It's not common to find a good chicken based hotpot as the hotpot market is dominated by beef and seafood. The chicken soup is rich and full of flavor. The chicken is juicy and tender - perfect match with the sesame sauce. The highlight for me was definitely the vegetables - decent variety and excellent quality - lovely textures and natural sweetness. The waiter told me that the vegetables are locally sourced for freshness. Oh, and it doesnt hurt to look at the Victoria Harbour while dining.

One tip for the tourist from Japan - confirmed with the staff, you can also earn stamps with your Japan membership card!

A very decent Japanese Restaurant in Harbour City. It locates beside the Victoria Harbour. Perfect view and nice Collagen chicken hot pot. Special food design of the other menus also. Cocktails there are up to standard. The price is a relatively high but reasonable for decent Japanese food. Range from 200-400 per head.
Nice decorated Victoria harbor view Japanese hotpot restaurant is best for Friday dinner with great Suntory Premium Malts beer and nice food.
Atmosphere is good n comfortable. Restaurant has good harbour view. The booth seat  is not enough lighting.
Not worth the price, food tasted blend , seafood wasn't fresh , service was really average. Won't come back

reviews.text:
The best shopping mall in Hong Kong:
1. itself + 6 more shopping malls, all inter-connected by enclosed air-conditioned walkways
2. Accessible by train, bus, minibuses, bicycles, private car (tons of parking space)
3. friendly affordable prices - not the Landmark or Pacific Place
It's easy to go around the place, convenient, but sometimes feel like the mall is kind of small.

It's the biggest mall in the region. Its been undergoing gentrification over the past few years. Local unique shops are being replaced by luxury chains. Car park is big but fills up quickly, and is expensive.
New Town Plaza Phase I is where you find the important shopping, City Super and lower level restaurant hall. There is direct access from the MTR Station and Shatin Park.
At Parkview : delicious food and good service👍

reviews.text: 商店按分類排列👍🏻
非常多內地客😥

成個商場嘅格局越嚟越似海港城，已經為自由行，而唔係再為沙田居民而設。
除非你真係好想買名牌，或者上食層食嘢，否則都係唔嚟好過！
小心俾自由行嘅巨型拖喼轆到隻腳， 成個商場比較行得舒服嘅係citysuper，起碼自由行唔會喺度買食材然後返屋企煮飯！

reviews.text: 成日都講係香港食日本野都係唔好抱咁大期望，但係要頂著日本條癮，久唔久食日本菜是常態。呢間日本品牌過左黎香港，係日本當地食，的確好好味，材料新鮮偏向清淡，夠晒健，大大份，食完好滿足。但係，一到香港，OMG，食材份量大減。嗱，刺身真係考刀功，薄到透光，咁你食到咩呢？連最門面既味噌湯，我夠膽講，全世界最細碗，講真，真係唔好當送俾人咁大方，兩三啖已經飲晒，倒不如慳返洗少隻碗仔好過。兒童杯仲大過隻碗。碗飯細到呢...
食材幾靚，但份量偏少，二人份量嘅鍋物唔係好夠食... (相已經係咁多)
A bit expensive but they do serve good food and good service
食材新鮮， 美人鍋很好吃， 套餐則沒有驚喜。 全部食物都很貴，可能是沙田餐廳的特點 吧。
Fair enough with the price and service
